KWANONGOMA - The AmaZulu royals are meeting on Wednesday to discuss a successor to King Goodwill Zwelithini. The next monarch will be chosen by the current regent, Queen Mantombi Dlamini. GALLERY: Remembering King Goodwill Zwelithini It's expected the announcement will be made in the next few days. President Cyril Ramaphasa and Traditional Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma are set to visit the palace, to discuss the authorisation of the next AmaZulu monarch.